=Ruy Lopez Main Line=

With White preparing to strike in the centre with d4, Black's king typically vacates the premises with [[/8...O-O|8...O-O]]. The old-fashioned move is [[/8...Na5|8...Na5]], which may transpose, but the loss of control over d4 may allow White to save a tempo by omitting h3.

[[/8...Bg4|8...Bg4]] is seen from time to time, discouraging an instant d4 by White. White will probably play d3 as a temporary measure, aiming to bring the queens knight to the kingside to evict the bishop in order to achieve d4.

